description: From French franciser (“to frenchify”), from France + -iser. Equivalent to France +‎ -ize.

verbs.description: francize (third-person singular simple present francizes, present participle francizing, simple past and past participle francized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) Synonym of frenchify, to make French or more French-like.
(intransitive) Synonym of frenchify, to become French or more French-like.
